OL,3,CWheelchair-user says Blue Badge fraud
OL,4,C'ruins lives'
OL,6,F"It'll either be someone who's
OL,7,Fborrowing mum's disabled badge because
OL,8,Fthey're doing her shopping, or they're
OL,9,Fpulled into a disabled parking space,
OL,10,Fusually in a supermarket car park,
OL,11,Fbecause they're 'only going to be a
OL,12,Ffew minutes', which is the usual
OL,13,Fexcuse.
OL,15,F"But I wonder how those people would
OL,16,Ffeel if I parked across their driveway
OL,17,Fjust for a few minutes when they're
OL,18,Fanxious to get out of their house in a
OL,19,Fhurry."
